alls with adds where the tank had 2 mobs beating on her and my cheal landed rather late. I figured the druid would spot heal, but since he hasn't, I sent em a tell not to sleep, I'm relying on him to spot heal.<br><br>&quot;I'm not sleeping&quot; he says.<br><br>Next 3 mobs, He throws gheals whent the tank hits 2 red on a single mob, every time. My cheal efficiency goes to hell in a handbasket, my frustration goes up exponentially every time my cheal lands at 3 or more red on the tank with one mob beating on him.<br><br>Is the concept of a spot heal so goddamn difficult to grasp? Hasn't the druid done it at all in at least 51 levels? 1 mob - lay the hell off. 2-3 mobs beating on the tank, hp dropping fast, throw a gheal or a chloroblast to make sure the tank lives long enough for cheal to land. ELEMENTARY! I'm not sure if I should mention that not once has the druid ever even attempted to heal the chanter, not even with chanter agroed and me tied up in a cheal...<br><br>So we get 3 adds at lower dogs and we all call EVAC, EVAC, EVAC!!! Drood gets in the middle of the group and starts casting a group port. Not evac, mind you - a port. When asked later, he said he thought the casting time difference between port and succor wasn't enough for it to matter... later told me in tells that he never had to evac before and that he calls all his ports evacs anyway.<br><br>Total wipeout at lower dogs cause, naturally, his port didn't go off in time. Even though me, rodg, tank and a monk went down before him trying to give him time to cast.<br><br>So we try it doing cr, me, him, chanter, and a warrior we picked up. We drop down to the first room to try and fight our way in. Chanter goes down early, 2 dogs there, we call evac again. What does Muffinz cast? Yup, you guessed it, you get $100! A regular port! Which casts just long enough to give the warrior time to die.<br><br>Before the night was over I died twice, warrior died twice, chanter died 3 or 4 times, not sure, druid died twice, and monks ate one death each. We ended up getting our corpses summoned by Larrs, a 60 necro from DH if I remember correctly.<br><br>To add insult to injury, after i went through some 8 peridots in that camp Rodg, who was masterlooting that night, logged without bothering to split pp he looted or any paws/scalps for cash. /sigh<br><br>Now, my questions are this:<br>How does a 51+ druid get to that level without knowing how to evac? It's his one goddamn role in the group, how do you NOT know how to do it?<br>How does the same druid not know how to spot heal?<br>Why am I always the one who gets stuck with a retard druid to begin with? <p><center><img src="http://devineclan.clanpages.com/signature.gif"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ukathrynnducharme.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kathrynn DuCharme</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 174<br> <font color=#333333>(12/30/01 4:48:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Retarded druids PISS me off</span><hr size=1> One hint..<br><br>Dont do pickup groups!<br><br>Thats a horrible story and reminds me of the pickup groups i did with my cleric :p <p><P><table width="262" border="4" height="102" align="center" bordercolor="#000000" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0"><tr>                               <td height="74" width="77%">                               <div align="center">                               <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b><font color="#0000CD"> Kathrynn</b><br><b>Krista Du'Charme<B></font></b></font><br>                               <b><font color="#990099" size="2">Enchantress and Cleric Extraordinair